WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:03.635
<i> Mike sr.: Mary!</i>
<i> My program is starting!</i>

00:03.704 --> 00:05.904
<i>Adult mark: The old man would</i>
<i> take a break from radio news</i>

00:05.973 --> 00:07.973
By watching tv news.
Mary: Here you go.

00:08.042 --> 00:12.043
<i>- His one escape from reality</i>
<i> was more reality!</i>

00:12.045 --> 00:13.912
<i> Reporter: Philippines dictator</i>
<i> ferdinand marcos</i>

00:14.048 --> 00:15.314
<i> Is in exile in hawaii</i>

00:15.449 --> 00:17.115
<i>As evidence mounts against him.</i>

00:17.184 --> 00:20.185
- Good god! Isn't that where
your little friend is from?

00:20.221 --> 00:22.387
They're having a hell
of a hard time over there.

00:22.423 --> 00:24.256
- I dare say they must be
having some hard time

00:24.258 --> 00:26.591
If they leave their weather
for ours.

00:26.593 --> 00:28.861
<i> Reporter: ...Be the first</i>
nuclear
<i>power plant in the philippines.</i>

00:28.863 --> 00:31.330
<i> The first lady, imelda marcos,</i>
<i>purchased millions of dollars--</i>

00:31.465 --> 00:33.732
<i>Adult mark: Back then, all eyes</i>
<i> were on the marcos family</i>

00:33.867 --> 00:35.367
<i> In the philippines,</i>

00:35.436 --> 00:38.736
<i> Which meant all eyes in</i>
<i> our class were on ritchie.</i>

00:38.873 --> 00:40.939
[chalk scrapes, clunks loudly]

00:41.075 --> 00:43.675
- [clears throat] I know
we've all been hearing

00:43.811 --> 00:45.978
About the philippines
in the news.

00:46.113 --> 00:48.413
Does anyone know
what a dictator is?

00:48.416 --> 00:50.382
- You mean like sister rose?

00:50.384 --> 00:52.684
[all giggle]

00:52.820 --> 00:54.920
<i> Sister margaret: This is no</i>
<i> laughing matter, missy.</i>

00:55.055 --> 00:58.323
Ritchie, what can you tell
the class about your homeland?

00:59.393 --> 01:01.359
- Uh, I don't really remember
that much.

01:01.429 --> 01:03.061
<i> - Oh! Come, now, ritchie.</i>

01:03.064 --> 01:05.497
One doesn't escape a dictator
and forget about it.

01:06.767 --> 01:08.834
- I, uh, um...

01:10.471 --> 01:12.771
Remember that it was hot?
- Wow.

01:12.906 --> 01:15.240
I feel so much smarter now.

01:15.242 --> 01:17.276
[class titters]

01:17.411 --> 01:19.711
- Well, it was a scorching hot
day when his family escaped...

01:19.747 --> 01:22.647
In a boat...
Over shark-infested waters.

01:23.717 --> 01:25.617
- [awkwardly] we flew.

01:25.619 --> 01:27.385
- Wait... Go on, mark.

01:27.387 --> 01:29.588
- They were on the run
from president marcos -

01:29.590 --> 01:32.924
A cross between the godfather
and darth vader!

01:32.960 --> 01:34.460
<i> He and his wife imelda stole</i>
<i> billions</i>

01:34.595 --> 01:36.395
<i> From people just like ritchie.</i>

01:36.530 --> 01:38.530
You know, she was so rich,
the first lady

01:38.599 --> 01:41.933
Had three thousand shoes.
- Three thousand shoes

01:41.969 --> 01:44.335
Or three thousand pairs
of shoes?

01:44.337 --> 01:47.339
- What's the difference?
- Three thousand shoes.

01:47.341 --> 01:49.174
- Ritchie?

01:49.309 --> 01:51.076
- I don't know.

01:51.145 --> 01:54.479
- Uh, three thousand pairs.
That's six thousand shoes!

01:54.482 --> 01:57.816
And that's pretty much
the story of the philippines.

01:57.951 --> 01:59.818
- Huh.

01:59.820 --> 02:03.421
Thank you, ritchie,
for sharing your heritage.

02:04.625 --> 02:07.960
It is important for us
to celebrate other cultures.

02:07.962 --> 02:10.962
That is why we are going
to have...

02:12.065 --> 02:13.432
A heritage fair!

02:13.434 --> 02:15.433
[chalkboard brush rubs]

02:15.469 --> 02:19.238
<i> I want everyone to pair up</i>
<i> and present their culture</i>

02:19.373 --> 02:21.640
<i> To the rest of the class.</i>

02:21.642 --> 02:23.274
Where are your family from,
gary?

02:23.310 --> 02:25.043
- Ireland.

02:25.045 --> 02:27.145
- Tina?
- England.

02:27.181 --> 02:28.579
- Ooh.

02:28.581 --> 02:31.115
- England and ireland.

02:31.152 --> 02:32.951
Tsk. Mixed marriage.

02:33.086 --> 02:35.387
- That, children,
is what we call

02:35.389 --> 02:37.856
Multiculturalism. Hmm.

02:37.858 --> 02:39.591
<i>Adult mark: The united nations,</i>
<i> we were not.</i>

02:39.627 --> 02:41.125
[bell rings]

02:41.162 --> 02:43.061
- Oh, and don't forget
to say your prayers

02:43.063 --> 02:45.296
For the good catholics
of the philippines,

02:45.332 --> 02:47.065
<i> And ritchie.</i>

02:47.201 --> 02:48.600
[low hum of chatter]

02:48.735 --> 02:51.135
- Our project is gonna be
the best one ever.

02:52.573 --> 02:54.305
See ya.
- See ya.

02:55.609 --> 02:56.874
[ritchie sighs, chair scrapes]

02:56.911 --> 02:58.309
[bag thuds, zipper buzzes]

02:59.613 --> 03:01.479
<i> Reporter: More unrest in</i>
<i> manilla as the protestors</i>

03:01.549 --> 03:03.815
<i>Took to the streets to demand</i>
<i> action. [gunshots pop]</i>

03:03.884 --> 03:05.417
[tv clicks off]

03:05.486 --> 03:07.819
- Hey! We need to see that.
Commercial: Thomas amusements!

03:07.955 --> 03:10.756
<i>Over 15 rides for family fun!</i>

03:10.758 --> 03:13.157
Coming to st. John's on Friday!
- Ha!

03:13.194 --> 03:15.193
I wanna go to the circus!

03:15.229 --> 03:17.295
- It's not a circus.
It's just rides.

03:17.364 --> 03:19.831
Dad gets a family pass
every year from the station,

03:20.935 --> 03:23.501
But I don't do rides.

03:24.771 --> 03:26.972
I'm not afraid of heights,
I'm... I'm afraid of lows.

03:27.041 --> 03:29.508
It's falling to my death
that I have a problem with.

03:29.510 --> 03:31.075
[awkward chuckle]

03:32.413 --> 03:34.580
I can watch you have fun from
the safety of the ground.

03:34.715 --> 03:37.181
- Can I ask fox?
It's a family pass

03:37.218 --> 03:38.950
And I need someone
to ride with.

03:38.953 --> 03:41.653
- [sighs] fine,
but that isn't important now.

03:42.957 --> 03:44.990
[paper rustles]
[mark exhale]

03:45.059 --> 03:47.292
<i> Mrs. Perez: Boys!</i>

03:47.361 --> 03:49.861
Move your stuff! Dinner!

03:49.863 --> 03:52.397
<i> Adult mark: My favourite words</i>
<i> at ritchie's house.</i>

03:52.399 --> 03:54.366
<i> Back home, the only spice</i>
<i> in our food was salt,</i>

03:54.501 --> 03:56.067
Mary: Supper!

03:56.103 --> 03:57.736
<i> - And the occasional cigarette</i>
<i> ash.</i>

03:57.738 --> 04:00.138
<i> My supper was usually</i>
<i>the same colour as the plate.</i>

04:00.274 --> 04:03.008
<i> Ritchie's house opened up</i>
<i> my virgin tastebuds</i>

04:03.077 --> 04:05.477
<i> To a world of colour</i>
<i> and flavour.</i>

04:05.479 --> 04:07.912
<i> My favourite was sweet</i>
<i> filipino spaghetti.</i>

04:07.982 --> 04:09.748
<i> It had little hot dogs</i>

04:09.817 --> 04:11.817
<i> And the sauce tasted</i>
<i> like melted Halloween candy.</i>

04:11.952 --> 04:14.085
- Thank you, lord,
for this food

04:14.154 --> 04:17.122
And the guests with whom
we share our food...

04:17.257 --> 04:19.524
Every night this week.

04:20.728 --> 04:23.028
<i> In your name we pray.</i>

04:23.097 --> 04:24.729
The perez family: Amen.

04:26.500 --> 04:28.166
- [mouth full] amen.

04:28.168 --> 04:31.269
♪♪♪

04:31.305 --> 04:33.204
[dog barks, birds chirp,
lawnmower rumbles]

04:33.274 --> 04:34.640
<i> Adult mark: I was stuffed,</i>

04:34.775 --> 04:37.909
<i> And mrs. Perez had also had</i>
<i> her fill... Of me!</i>

04:37.945 --> 04:39.978
- Mark, your mother's coming
to get you.

04:40.113 --> 04:41.746
- Oh, forgot, she can't.

04:41.782 --> 04:44.549
Our car is broken.
I think I need a ride.

04:44.618 --> 04:47.218
- I told him you wouldn't mind,
mom.

04:47.254 --> 04:49.588
- Your father will take him.

04:49.590 --> 04:51.590
- Don't forget to tell your
parents about the thing.

04:51.725 --> 04:53.791
- Oh? What thing?

04:53.827 --> 04:56.127
- Mark's got tickets
to the circus this Friday.

04:56.196 --> 04:57.863
<i> Mr. Perez: Don't you remember?</i>

04:57.998 --> 05:00.098
You have to help with
the lechon on Friday.

05:00.134 --> 05:02.900
- Ooh, what's that?
- We put a whole pig on a spit

05:02.936 --> 05:05.269
Then turn it until
my arm falls off.

05:05.271 --> 05:07.205
- A pig roast? I'm in!

05:07.207 --> 05:09.274
I'll bring my don ho records.

05:09.343 --> 05:12.009
- Oh, our church group
is welcoming

05:12.046 --> 05:13.845
Some newly arrived kababayans.

05:14.915 --> 05:17.682
Uh, I'm sorry, mark,
it's a filipino thing.

05:17.684 --> 05:20.018
- Well, I'm practically
filipino!

05:20.020 --> 05:21.452
Right, ritchie?

05:23.590 --> 05:26.324
- Let's get you home, buddy.

05:26.360 --> 05:28.694
- So where do we stand
on the circus?

05:28.829 --> 05:30.595
- Oh, thank you so much
for the invitation,

05:30.597 --> 05:32.530
But it's going to be a no.

05:32.566 --> 05:35.434
Family obligation.
- But mom!

05:35.569 --> 05:37.636
- I'm sorry, mark!

05:37.638 --> 05:40.438
♪♪♪

05:40.474 --> 05:42.574
<i> Adult mark: I might not have</i>
<i> been able to take a hint,</i>

05:42.643 --> 05:44.776
<i> But I always took a ride.</i>

05:48.549 --> 05:50.916
- [sighs] I got a sandwich
and chips. What'd you get?

05:51.051 --> 05:52.984
- Adobo.

05:53.020 --> 05:54.619
- [excited] oh!

05:54.621 --> 05:56.588
We should add an adobo panel
to our project.

05:57.791 --> 05:59.891
[chip bag crinkles]
- about that...

06:00.026 --> 06:01.526
- Oh? What?

06:01.595 --> 06:03.461
- Mom doesn't think we should
work on

06:03.597 --> 06:05.497
Our heritage day project
together anymore.

06:05.499 --> 06:07.498
- What? Why?

06:07.534 --> 06:09.868
- [sighs] she said it was
my heritage,

06:09.870 --> 06:11.636
So I should present it
on my own.

06:11.672 --> 06:14.071
[chair scrapes]
- nerd tax!

06:17.277 --> 06:19.277
What's going on?

06:19.412 --> 06:21.813
Don't tell me you two turds
are getting a divorce?

06:21.849 --> 06:23.448
We got a circus date.

06:23.583 --> 06:25.650
- I'm not going.

06:25.686 --> 06:28.086
- So, it's just me and him?

06:29.356 --> 06:31.556
This isn't a date!
You hear me, you little weirdo?

06:31.625 --> 06:33.291
- You're the one who said
"date."

06:33.427 --> 06:35.059
- No, I didn't!
- Yeah, you did.

06:35.095 --> 06:37.094
You said, "we got a circus
date."

06:37.131 --> 06:39.297
- That was when it was
the three of us.

06:39.366 --> 06:41.766
You probably set it up
like this, you little pervert.

06:41.769 --> 06:44.836
- I didn't even wanna go
in the first place!

06:44.872 --> 06:47.038
Sure as heck I don't want
a date with you!

06:47.074 --> 06:49.407
- Good! I don't either.

06:49.410 --> 06:51.776
- Good!
- Better not be late for it!

06:51.779 --> 06:53.978
- Okay!
- I'm serious!

06:53.980 --> 06:55.746
- Fine!
- Good!

06:55.783 --> 06:57.548
[footsteps stomp away]

07:00.387 --> 07:02.721
- That's totally a date.

07:02.856 --> 07:04.288
- Hmm.

07:05.625 --> 07:08.393
Ugh! Mom, what's for supper?

07:08.462 --> 07:10.394
- Ah, a bit o' meat fried up
in a pan.

07:10.431 --> 07:12.264
- Mmm.
- [sighs] exotic.

07:12.266 --> 07:14.098
- [reads] "the-

07:14.168 --> 07:16.334
Family spent hundreds of--

07:16.336 --> 07:18.403
On their--

07:18.405 --> 07:19.805
And a lavish--

07:19.940 --> 07:21.272
With real--

07:21.308 --> 07:23.008
Pearls."

07:23.010 --> 07:25.610
Mark, where are my words?

07:25.612 --> 07:27.345
<i> Mark: I'm sorry.</i>

07:27.347 --> 07:29.281
I was just using it
for my heritage day project

07:29.283 --> 07:31.216
On the philippines.
- Philippines?

07:31.285 --> 07:33.417
That's not your heritage.

07:33.454 --> 07:35.921
You're a newfoundlander,
my son.

07:35.923 --> 07:38.356
I mean, this place
is practically maggoty

07:38.358 --> 07:39.891
With culture.

07:39.927 --> 07:41.726
I mean, do a project on us!

07:41.795 --> 07:44.162
- No, pop. It's gotta be
about somewhere real.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.897
He can't do newfoundland.
- Real?!

07:45.933 --> 07:47.932
Well, what's this? Narnia?

07:47.968 --> 07:52.237
My god, newfoundlanders
practically invented culture.

07:52.306 --> 07:54.039
We used to have
our own country

07:54.174 --> 07:57.042
'til that asshole voted it
out of existence.

07:57.044 --> 07:58.843
<i> Adult mark: Newfoundland</i>
<i> was once its own country,</i>

07:58.879 --> 08:00.778
<i> But we became canada's</i>
<i> 10th province</i>

08:00.814 --> 08:03.215
<i> By a vote of just 52%.</i>

08:03.350 --> 08:05.950
<i>A fact that was like a constant</i>
<i> gas leak at our house,</i>

08:05.986 --> 08:07.919
<i> And pop was the match.</i>

08:08.054 --> 08:10.522
- All right, all right.
Look, I voted to join canada

08:10.524 --> 08:12.991
So that we'd have a better
future for all of us.

08:13.126 --> 08:16.194
- And what did canada
ever do for me?

08:16.329 --> 08:18.330
- Oh, that reminds me.

08:18.332 --> 08:20.131
Your canada pension cheque
came.

08:20.267 --> 08:22.801
- Oh god, I've been looking
all over for that!

08:22.803 --> 08:24.602
Hey, mark, come with me.

08:24.638 --> 08:26.872
<i> I've got a trunk full</i>
<i> of culture.</i>

08:27.007 --> 08:29.040
[footsteps recede]
- [whispers] do I have to go?

08:29.175 --> 08:31.009
- I don't see how you're
gettin' out of it.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.278
<i> Pop: Mark! Get your arse</i>
<i> in here!</i>

08:37.384 --> 08:38.750
L rings]

08:40.354 --> 08:43.021
- The philippines:
The pearl of the orient

08:43.090 --> 08:45.757
With over 7000 islands

08:45.759 --> 08:48.492
And 300 volcanoes!

08:52.232 --> 08:56.234
♪♪♪

08:56.369 --> 08:58.103
It's supposed to blow.

08:58.105 --> 09:00.071
- Believe me, it blows.

09:00.206 --> 09:01.940
<i> [class titters]</i>
<i> sister margaret: Fox!</i>

09:01.942 --> 09:04.242
Well, uh, ritchie,

09:04.377 --> 09:06.444
We get the picture.

09:06.446 --> 09:07.912
Mark, you're next.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.514
[chair scrapes back]

09:09.583 --> 09:11.182
<i> Adult mark: Ritchie was the</i>
<i> first person ever rescued</i>

09:11.318 --> 09:13.718
<i> From a volcano</i>
<i> that didn't erupt.</i>

09:13.720 --> 09:15.987
- [sighs]
[curtains scrape shut]

09:19.459 --> 09:20.992
[overhead projector clicks on]

09:22.128 --> 09:24.262
Before canada joined
newfoundland,

09:24.264 --> 09:26.063
<i> We were our own country,</i>

09:27.100 --> 09:29.334
With our own passports...

09:30.470 --> 09:32.203
And our own currency...

09:32.339 --> 09:33.872
[bills rustle and scatter]

09:36.410 --> 09:38.009
[class murmurs]

09:38.078 --> 09:40.711
And our own songs.

09:43.216 --> 09:45.449
[loudly] and our own songs!

09:45.485 --> 09:47.418
[door creaks open]

09:49.489 --> 09:51.222
["the ryans and the pittmans"
plays]

09:51.224 --> 09:53.358
Adults: ♪ we'll rant
and we'll roar ♪

09:53.493 --> 09:55.493
♪ like true newfoundlanders

09:55.495 --> 09:57.128
♪ we'll rant and we'll roar

09:57.164 --> 09:59.864
♪ on deck and below

10:00.000 --> 10:02.167
- ♪ oooooooh !

10:02.169 --> 10:04.268
Long live newfoundland!

10:04.338 --> 10:06.905
[class joins in]
long live newfoundland!

10:07.040 --> 10:09.707
Long live newfoundland!

10:09.776 --> 10:11.776
Long live newfoundland!

10:11.778 --> 10:14.445
- All right! All right!
There'll be no riots today.

10:14.514 --> 10:17.582
Mark, that's very well done!

10:17.584 --> 10:18.917
An a for you, mark.

10:19.052 --> 10:21.218
- [gleeful laugh] hey!
All right, b'y?!

10:21.254 --> 10:23.121
All right, b'y!
- Thank you.

10:23.190 --> 10:25.123
Tsk.

10:25.192 --> 10:27.058
[volcano bubbles]
- tsk!

10:28.194 --> 10:30.662
[bubbling]

10:30.664 --> 10:33.764
♪♪♪

10:33.800 --> 10:36.734
[spit creaks]

10:36.870 --> 10:39.070
<i> Mrs. Perez: Ritchie!</i>

10:39.106 --> 10:41.272
This is ron and jenny,

10:41.408 --> 10:43.708
And that's your tita
and your tito.

10:43.843 --> 10:46.878
They're from batangas,
near the taal volcano!

10:47.013 --> 10:48.880
- You guys like video games?

10:50.283 --> 10:53.885
Mrs. Perez: [chuckles] ron's
still figuring out his english.

10:53.954 --> 10:57.021
Ron, ano ba gusto mo gawin?
- Patintero?

10:57.024 --> 10:59.891
- Oh, ritchie, patintero's
a game. It's like red rover!

11:00.961 --> 11:03.360
- Oh! You guys know pac-man?

11:06.700 --> 11:08.633
- Ugh... Doh.

11:08.702 --> 11:11.636
[carnival music plays,
indistinct chatter]

11:11.705 --> 11:13.405
[laughter, ride whirs]

11:14.741 --> 11:15.974
Adult mark: There were only
two things

11:16.109 --> 11:17.975
<i> That scared me more</i>
<i> than the scrambler.</i>

11:18.011 --> 11:19.643
<i> One, having a date with fox...</i>

11:19.680 --> 11:22.379
- This is not a date!
- I know!

11:22.416 --> 11:25.049
<i> Adult mark: And two,</i>
<i> not having a date with fox.</i>

11:25.052 --> 11:27.318
- That one looks cool.

11:27.320 --> 11:29.320
<i> Adult mark: The scrambler</i>
<i> was not my speed.</i>

11:29.456 --> 11:30.855
- Totally.

11:30.857 --> 11:33.091
How 'bout that one?

11:33.093 --> 11:34.825
<i> Adult mark: My speed</i>
<i> was parked.</i>

11:36.529 --> 11:38.062
- Why don't we start on
the berry-go-round

11:38.065 --> 11:39.797
And work our way up.

11:39.866 --> 11:42.967
Besides, no one we know'll
see us on that one.

11:42.969 --> 11:44.936
<i> Worker: Win a prize</i>
<i> for your sweetie!</i>

11:45.071 --> 11:46.271
<i> Step right up!</i>

11:46.406 --> 11:49.207
[distant scream, ride whirs]

11:50.977 --> 11:52.811
<i> Woman: Over here! Over here!</i>

11:52.946 --> 11:55.013
[grass crunches underfoot]

11:56.216 --> 11:59.284
- [sighs] this is no scrambler.

11:59.286 --> 12:01.152
[grunts] ungh!

12:01.188 --> 12:03.421
[hard thud]

12:03.556 --> 12:04.889
I don't like this game.

12:06.026 --> 12:07.292
- [in tagalog] he's a soft
conyo kid.

12:07.427 --> 12:09.360
Wouldn't survive a day
back home.

12:09.362 --> 12:11.095
- I can't speak tagalog,

12:11.131 --> 12:14.064
But I know when I'm being
made fun of.

12:14.101 --> 12:17.102
- You're not filipino.
- I was born there.

12:17.237 --> 12:18.770
- You're like lechon.

12:18.905 --> 12:21.439
Brown the outside,
white in the inside.

12:21.574 --> 12:23.007
[snorts softly]

