14:01.140 --> 14:02.941
Kiss is not a newfoundland
band!

14:02.943 --> 14:06.077
- They are so! Gene simmons,
the fella with the big tongue,

14:06.079 --> 14:08.012
Well, he's married
to shannon tweed

14:08.081 --> 14:10.281
And she's a newfoundlander!

14:10.317 --> 14:13.751
So, kiss are newfoundlanders
by marriage!

14:13.886 --> 14:15.820
- Oh, for god's sake.
- Agh.

14:15.889 --> 14:17.222
Know-it-all!

14:17.357 --> 14:19.490
[phone rings,
teapot and cup clink]

14:19.492 --> 14:21.826
Phone, mary.
- Thank you.

14:23.396 --> 14:25.029
Hello.
- Hello, mary.

14:25.164 --> 14:26.864
This is ritchie's mom.

14:26.933 --> 14:29.500
<i>I was just wondering if ritchie</i>
<i> was at your house.</i>

14:29.636 --> 14:32.170
- No. I thought he was
at the circus with mark.

14:32.172 --> 14:34.438
<i> Mrs. Perez: Ritchie was not</i>
<i> allowed to go to the circus.</i>

14:34.474 --> 14:36.307
- Oh, the little bugger.

14:36.442 --> 14:37.976
<i> Mrs. Perez: I'm going to go</i>
<i> there.</i>

14:38.111 --> 14:40.177
- I'll join you. Hmm.

14:40.179 --> 14:42.079
[handset clatters]

14:43.283 --> 14:46.517
- Splash the frog, win a prize!

14:46.519 --> 14:49.220
[carnival music plays,
indistinct chatter]

14:49.222 --> 14:52.123
- Don't watch.
- Why not?

14:52.192 --> 14:54.292
- It makes me nervous
if you watch.

14:54.294 --> 14:56.194
- God's sakes, just hit it.

14:57.397 --> 14:59.663
[apparatus clunks loudly]

14:59.699 --> 15:01.532
- [laughs] pathetic!

15:01.534 --> 15:03.067
Here.

15:03.103 --> 15:06.004
<i> [indistinct chatter</i>
<i> and laughter]</i>

15:06.006 --> 15:07.605
There's a trick
to all these games.

15:07.740 --> 15:09.540
You gotta hit 'em just right.

15:09.609 --> 15:11.909
[decisive thud, frog clatters,
bell rings]

15:12.879 --> 15:15.379
- Winner! Big prize!

15:16.516 --> 15:18.082
- How 'bout that one?

15:18.217 --> 15:20.651
For ritchie -
he has a pet snake.

15:20.654 --> 15:22.620
- There you go, young fella.
- Thank you.

15:22.755 --> 15:25.089
- Have a nice date now.
- Frig off!

15:25.224 --> 15:26.957
<i> Worker: Third times the charm!</i>

15:26.993 --> 15:29.127
[indistinct chatter,
wheel rattles]

15:29.262 --> 15:32.229
[water sprays]

15:33.300 --> 15:35.566
- On your marks, get set...

15:35.702 --> 15:37.234
Go!

15:37.236 --> 15:39.636
[sucking on straw]

15:41.007 --> 15:44.242
<i> [carnival music plays,</i>
<i> indistinct chatter]</i>

15:44.377 --> 15:46.511
Argh! Yeah, brain freeze.

15:46.646 --> 15:49.313
- [laughs] why are you so lame?

15:50.583 --> 15:53.784
- Ritchie can down
the whole thing in one gulp.

15:53.853 --> 15:55.186
- 'kay, fess up.

15:55.188 --> 15:57.288
Why couldn't he come?

15:57.423 --> 15:59.690
- His mom doesn't like me.

15:59.726 --> 16:01.658
- She's stupid then.

16:03.263 --> 16:05.496
I mean, not that stupid.

16:06.632 --> 16:09.200
Enough stallin'.
It's time for the scrambler.

16:09.202 --> 16:13.004
- I can't do the scrambler!
I told ritchie I'd wait!

16:13.006 --> 16:15.672
- 'kay. The ferris wheel it is,
then.

16:16.876 --> 16:18.342
Come on.

16:18.345 --> 16:20.144
Let's go.
Grab your stuff.

16:21.548 --> 16:23.014
Come on.

16:23.083 --> 16:25.950
<i> [indistinct chatter]</i>

16:28.021 --> 16:29.353
<i> Rider: Woo-hoo-hoo!</i>

16:29.389 --> 16:31.222
<i> Adult mark: Ritchie had</i>
<i> literally run away</i>

16:31.224 --> 16:33.624
<i> To join the circus.</i>

16:33.626 --> 16:35.826
<i> Meanwhile, my not-a-date</i>

16:35.895 --> 16:37.829
<i> Was starting to feel a lot</i>
<i> like...</i>

16:37.964 --> 16:39.897
<i> A date.</i>

16:39.899 --> 16:41.398
[door creaks shut,
bangs closed]

16:43.970 --> 16:45.302
[lock jams]

16:46.572 --> 16:48.439
<i> Rider: Whooooaaaaaaaa!</i>

16:50.676 --> 16:53.010
- Hey! This isn't so bad.

16:54.881 --> 16:56.314
Hey, look! It's ritchie!

16:56.449 --> 16:59.517
<i> Hey, ritchie! Up here!</i>

16:59.519 --> 17:01.853
[the pod rattles and creaks]

17:01.988 --> 17:03.387
- No! What're you doing?!

17:03.390 --> 17:05.123
[hyperventilating] stop!

17:05.125 --> 17:07.558
- I never told you it spins?
Oops!

17:07.627 --> 17:09.427
- [panicked] stop!

17:09.429 --> 17:11.162
- [laughs] don't be such
a baby!

17:11.297 --> 17:13.898
[lever clunks]

17:14.033 --> 17:15.900
[the ride creaks to a stop]

17:17.137 --> 17:18.469
[rider screams]
- what's going on?!

17:18.604 --> 17:21.005
It's broken! Help! Help!

17:21.074 --> 17:22.906
Help! We're gonna die!

17:22.942 --> 17:24.909
We're gonna die!
- Hey, it's-it's okay.

17:25.044 --> 17:27.345
- [hyperventilating] no!
- So just calm down.

17:27.480 --> 17:29.279
- [gasping for air]
no, I can't look.

17:29.315 --> 17:31.615
- They just stop it
for a laugh.

17:32.752 --> 17:35.553
- Let my friends down!
- Jeez, b'y. Calm down.

17:35.688 --> 17:37.555
I'm just tryin' to do
the little fella a favour.

17:37.624 --> 17:39.256
He's on a date.

17:40.860 --> 17:42.427
- We're gonna die.
[panicked breaths]

17:43.763 --> 17:46.497
- C'mon. Just, just open
your eyes.

17:46.632 --> 17:48.966
- I can't.
- You can.

17:49.101 --> 17:51.602
[sweet, romantic music plays]

17:55.174 --> 17:58.109
<i> Adult mark: At that moment,</i>
<i> my fear of dying went away.</i>

17:58.244 --> 18:01.045
<i>It was replaced with another,</i>
<i> more terrifying one.</i>

18:01.047 --> 18:03.413
<i> A girl was holding my hand.</i>

18:05.652 --> 18:07.585
[romantic music swells]

18:07.654 --> 18:14.659
♪♪♪

18:14.661 --> 18:19.530
♪♪♪

18:19.665 --> 18:21.566
[door creaks open]

18:23.069 --> 18:25.336
[gate squeaks open]

18:26.606 --> 18:28.405
- Sorry! Didn't know
it was a date.

18:28.407 --> 18:30.174
- Shut up!

18:34.013 --> 18:36.080
- Thank you. Great view.

18:36.082 --> 18:39.484
Gave a whole new perspective
on... Everything.

18:43.689 --> 18:45.623
- All right.

18:45.692 --> 18:48.259
- What were you thinking
leaving like that?

18:48.394 --> 18:50.828
- Are you on a date?

18:50.963 --> 18:52.729
Both: It's not a date!

18:54.000 --> 18:55.633
- [speaking tagalog]

18:56.936 --> 18:59.670
I was worried sick.
Why did you leave your cousins?

19:00.773 --> 19:03.040
- You always tell me to fit in.

19:03.076 --> 19:05.076
Well, I do -

19:06.612 --> 19:08.579
With them.

19:08.581 --> 19:11.449
We're different,
but we're the same.

19:11.451 --> 19:13.551
There is a different kind
of same.

19:13.620 --> 19:15.686
- It's just that...

19:15.688 --> 19:17.788
I don't want you to forget
about home.

19:18.892 --> 19:20.725
- This is home, mom,

19:20.727 --> 19:22.660
Here with you.

19:24.797 --> 19:27.431
- I guess I've been pretty hard
on you, huh?

19:27.467 --> 19:29.800
- It's okay.

19:31.104 --> 19:33.203
- No, it's not.

19:35.975 --> 19:37.874
I have an idea.

19:37.911 --> 19:39.310
Come.

